b'Conclusion:\n\nMohamed Salah is a phenomenal player, but he\xe2\x80\x99s not exactly a winger. He never had the role of a Barca Neymar or even a Raphinha (as he\xe2\x80\x99s not asked to). He\xe2\x80\x99s more comparable to Mbappe, and post knee injury Cristiano Ronaldo (not in terms of quality but role).'

b'box is quite comparable (Salah\xe2\x80\x99s in or around the box more often but that can be contributed to Liverpool\xe2\x80\x99s time of possession and insane chance creation due to positional overloads).'

b'Salah\xe2\x80\x99s role isn\xe2\x80\x99t exactly that of a striker. He has more responsibilities. For contrast, here are Jamie Vardy\xe2\x80\x99s heatmaps for the last 4 seasons including this one. Obviously, Salah tends to be right sided, while Vardy\xe2\x80\x99s centrally. However, how often they are around or near the+ https://t.co/Mr3iMbDabI'

b'Even Sadio Man\xc3\xa9 has a similar role in terms of positioning (see heatmaps of his last 4 years including this one). Obviously, it\xe2\x80\x99s not an exact replica to Salah\xe2\x80\x99s due to their skill sets and qualities, but it\xe2\x80\x99s quite similar, just inverted (due to Klopp\xe2\x80\x99s system). https://t.co/KdNe81MWtF'

b'Mo gets many touches and receives the ball near or around the 18. This is exaggerated by Klopp\xe2\x80\x99s system and its chance creation (in part due to its emphasis on position, pressing, and creating numerical advantages). The insane end product is a result of this and Salah\xe2\x80\x99s quality'
